Package Presentation.Commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Command  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BackCommand
    Command, that sends user back to front page if a command value of the specified string key cannot be found.
    ChangePriceCommand
    Command that validates and handles admin change of price functionality
    CreateResponseCommand
    Command that handles the creation of a response.
    DeleteRequestCommand
    Command that handles the deletion of a specific request.
    DeleteResponseCommand
    Commands that handles the deletion of a specific response.
    FlatRoofFormCommand
    Command for loading flat roof form jsp including a list of available roofs
    FrontpageRedirectCommand
    Command that redirects a user to a proper frontpage
    GenerateReqCommand
    Command that handles generation of request based on user input
    InclinedRoofFormCommand
    Command for loading inclined roof form jsp including a list of available roofs
    InsertResponseCommand
    Command that handles the creation of a response.
    LoginCommand
    Command that that validates and logs in user
    LogoutCommand
    Command that logs a user out
    PrebuiltCarportCommand
    Command that creates a list of prebuilt carports to present in jsp file
    RegisterCommand
    Command that validates user input and registers user with the specified input
    ShopCommand
    Command that receives a request from prebuiltcarport.jsp Created a session containing ShoppingCart entity class Forward to shoppingcart.jsp
    ShowPricesCommand
    Command that fetches all available roofs and materials so they can be displayed on jsp page
    ShowRequestCommand
    Command that handles creation of BOM, SVG and total sell/buy-price after pressing show request.
    ShowRequestsCommand
    Command that shows a list of all requests
    ShowResponseCommand
    Command that retrieves a specifc response(User) Used when a user wants to see offer he has received on a carport.
    ShowResponsesCommand
    Command that retrieves all of the responses associated with a specifc user.
    UpdateResponsePriceCommand
    Command that allows a seller to update the price on a response(offer on a carport).
